moves.1. e4: I feel that this is one of the best games I have played. Articulator probably just underestimated me. If someone sees something that I did not, feel free to comment.
moves.1... d5: At this point he is trying to gain control of the center of the board.
moves.2. e5: So I move my king pawn to e5, something I hate having done to me.
moves.2... a6 3. d4 e6 4. a3 Ne7 5. Nc3 Nbc6 6: Probably not the best move move. I should have developed my king,knight or queen,bishop.
moves.6... b6 7. Bd3 Bb7 8. Be3 Qd7 9. Nf3 h6: Was not expecting a queen side castle.
moves.11... g5 12. b4: Applying pawn pressure to break up the wall of pieces he has built in front of his King.
moves.12... b5 13. a4: Maybe not the best move, but I want to keep applying pressure. I do not want him to finish developing his pieces for an attack, instead I want to be the one applying pressure.
moves.13... Nxb4 14. axb5 axb5 15. Bxb5 c6: Nice defensive move, but I have already started to break down his defence.
moves.16. Ba4: I had to retreat my bishop to keep his knight from capturing c2.
moves.16... Ng6 17. Nb3 Be7 18. Nc5: I move Nc5 to lure e7 bishop.
moves.19. dxc5 Nxe5 20. Qxb4 Nc4 21. Nb5: At this point I feel I have enough piece to push my attack. So I sacrifice my knight to open things up. I played this out many times and feel that this is what needed done to decapitate his King.
moves.26. Ra7+: He can't stop what is coming, but only prolong it.
